RIYADH: The General Presidency for the Affairs of the Holy Mosques has decided to reimpose social distancing measures in the Grand Mosque and the Prophet’s Mosque from 7 a.m. on Thursday. An official source at the presidency said that social distancing will be imposed between the worshippers to ensure the safety of visitors. The source said that all visitors and workers in the Two Holy Mosques should abide by the preventive measures by wearing masks, complying with the entrance hours according to the permits issued by the adopted applications, maintaining social distancing and abiding by the directives of the authorities working in the mosques.